transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you for calling Viagra. How can I assist you?

Speaker 2: Yes, this is W.H. Johnson.

Speaker 1: Hi.

Speaker 2: And what I'm calling for is I need to cancel my prescription.

Speaker 1: Okay. And what is the reason for the cancellation?

Speaker 2: Is it that you have enough supply or why not?

Speaker 1: No, it doesn't do – it hasn't done anything.

Speaker 2: And then I just got another shipment in,

Speaker 1: and I didn't know I had to call and say something or what to do.

Speaker 2: I thought we just had to just reorder.

Speaker 1: Okay. It's only because you are taking 50 milligrams.

Speaker 2: What I can go ahead and do for you, William,

Speaker 1: is that I can send you 10 free pills of our new Viagra AGB, up 100 milligrams.

Speaker 2: Those are more potent.

Speaker 1: And I'll pause your VIP until April, okay?

Speaker 2: Hopefully that works for you.

Speaker 1: No, I'm not going to do it because I was taking two of those, no matter what.

Speaker 2: Yeah, but this one's different. This one's more potent.

Speaker 1: This one's different.

Speaker 2: So 100 milligrams has more strength compared to taking two.

Speaker 1: No, that's all right. Don't even worry about it.

Speaker 2: It has worked for a lot of customers when they take the 100 instead of the 50.

Speaker 1: No, just don't worry about it. Just cancel it.

Speaker 2: Are you sure? Because I'll be sending it to you for free.

Speaker 1: No, that's okay. Just cancel my prescription.

Speaker 2: Okay. Well, you're all set. Have a good day. Bye.

Speaker 1: Okay, then.
